 although\nit is not as young as the youngest globular clusters associated with the\nSagittarius dwarf. The young age of NGC121 could result from delayed cluster\nformation in the Small Magellanic Cloud or result from the random survival of\nonly one example of an initially small number star clusters.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 7 Jan 2008 21:05:03 GMT"}],"update_date":"2008-01-09"}
