stars with\nAPEX, whereas SO is only detected in the oxygen-rich star WX Psc. This is the\nfirst multi-molecular observational proof that periodically shocked layers\nabove the photosphere of AGB stars show some chemical homogeneity, whatever the\nphotospheric C/O ratio and stage of evolution of the star.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 7 Jan 2008 21:14:54 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-11-13"}
